ottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":77,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":79,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Rio Chillham was born in 1508, in Kent, Kent, England. She married Paul Ward in 1539, in Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1590, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1508–1590":"1508–1590","1519–1583":"1519–1583","1540–1585":"1540–1585","Aft 1585":"pärast 1585","1583":"1583","1590":"1590","June 1583":"juuni 1583","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1508":"1508","1519":"1519","1539":"1539","1549":"1549","Chilham, Kent, England":"Chilham, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Kent, Kent, England":"Kent, Kent, England","Staplehurst, Maidstone district, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Staplehurst, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Chilham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1508–1590":"1508–1590","1519–1583":"1519–1583","1540–1585":"1540–1585","Aft 1585":"1585 jälkeen","1583":"1583","1590":"1590","June 1583":"kesäkuu 1583","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1587":"158